WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:03.003
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR: Oh, boy, oh, boy. You'll recall

00:03.046 --> 00:04.743
we last left our Jane
working with her father

00:04.787 --> 00:05.744
onThis Is Mars, which,
you'll recall, was a remake

00:05.788 --> 00:07.529
ofThe Passions
of Steve and Brenda,

00:07.572 --> 00:10.271
which, of course, was a remake
ofThe Passions of Santos.

00:10.314 --> 00:13.100
But the creative juices
weren't flowing for everyone.

00:13.143 --> 00:16.799
Mateo is really struggling
with his reading.

00:16.842 --> 00:18.714
He is quite far behind
the rest of the class.

00:18.757 --> 00:19.802
Just read a lot to him.

00:19.845 --> 00:22.109
Play word games.
Just engage him.

00:22.152 --> 00:24.720
And so Jane and Rafael tried
to put their feelings aside

00:24.763 --> 00:26.939
to focus on their son.Art?

00:26.983 --> 00:29.072
But this was easier said
than done for poor Jane.

00:29.116 --> 00:32.554
See, she still loved Rafael,
but he'd moved on,

00:32.597 --> 00:34.817
and Jane was trying to as well.

00:34.860 --> 00:36.558
JANE:
It was the first time
I've been with him in weeks

00:36.601 --> 00:38.212
where my heart
didn't just break.

00:38.255 --> 00:40.475
It was brief, but still,
there was a moment.

00:40.518 --> 00:42.390
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Also trying to move forward?

00:42.433 --> 00:44.218
Petra and J.R. See,

00:44.261 --> 00:45.741
J.R. lost her job
because Petra had lied.

00:45.784 --> 00:48.570
But they decided
to work through it.

00:48.613 --> 00:50.224
Aw, I heart them.

00:50.267 --> 00:52.400
Only problem?RAMOS: My mentor.

00:52.443 --> 00:54.315
She thinks she found me
a job opportunity.

00:54.358 --> 00:55.968
What? That's amazing.

00:56.012 --> 00:58.667
Thing is, the job's in Houston.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.234
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Also facing a big decision...

01:00.277 --> 01:03.193
Rafael and Jane let Mateo meet
his Aunt Luisa.

01:03.237 --> 01:05.021
But unfortunately...DENNIS: Rafael.

01:05.065 --> 01:07.676
It's Dennis. Do you know
where your sister is?

01:07.719 --> 01:09.199
Yes, I do.

01:09.243 --> 01:10.461
Well, we just found out

01:10.505 --> 01:12.289
that all the money
from Rose's Satin Road

01:12.333 --> 01:14.204
was funneled into an account
under her name.

01:14.248 --> 01:15.901
We think they're still
working together.

01:15.945 --> 01:18.078
I know!
Straight out of a telenovela,

01:18.121 --> 01:20.254
which this is, after all.

01:22.082 --> 01:24.954
When Jane Gloriana Villanueva
was 30 years old...

01:24.997 --> 01:26.129
I'm pregnant. Huh?

01:29.176 --> 01:30.525
Wait, what?

01:30.568 --> 01:32.396
I didn't even have sex.

01:32.440 --> 01:33.528
Okay, now I'm really confused.

01:33.571 --> 01:34.746
ROGELIO:
Jane!

01:34.790 --> 01:37.053
I have big news.

01:38.402 --> 01:39.969
Ah, I see.

01:40.012 --> 01:42.363
She's writing her novel.

01:42.406 --> 01:44.974
Sorry, I lost focus
for a second.

01:45.017 --> 01:47.585
Juggling a lot of things.So?

01:47.629 --> 01:49.457
What are you working on?

01:49.500 --> 01:51.459
Since Alba and Jorge
are on their honeymoon,

01:51.502 --> 01:54.201
I'm taking advantage of the
quiet time to work on my novel.

01:54.244 --> 01:55.202
Well, quiet time is over!

01:55.245 --> 01:57.029
The network liked your

01:57.073 --> 01:59.031
This Is Marsoutline so much,

01:59.075 --> 02:02.426
they want you
to write the pilot script.

02:02.470 --> 02:05.647
What? That's amazing.
Oh, my God.

02:05.690 --> 02:06.909
Are you serious?

02:11.479 --> 02:14.264
Mm!
So amazing.

02:14.308 --> 02:16.527
They did insist,
however,

02:16.571 --> 02:18.616
that you be paired
with a senior writer.

02:18.660 --> 02:20.618
Just to help guide you.

02:20.662 --> 02:23.621
Oh, I'll take all the guidance
I can get. Who'd they hire?

02:23.665 --> 02:27.190
It's actually Dina, since she
worked on the original Santos.

02:27.234 --> 02:30.976
Really? Dina's willing
to work with you again?

02:31.020 --> 02:32.195
Well...

02:32.239 --> 02:34.023
No way in hell.

02:34.066 --> 02:36.330
You never respected
me as a writer.

02:36.373 --> 02:38.462
I was constantly putting out
fires you created,

02:38.506 --> 02:40.334
and you cut me out

02:40.377 --> 02:42.031
of your American version
of The Passions of Santos

02:42.074 --> 02:43.554
even though I created it.

02:43.598 --> 02:46.470
To be honest, she called
the prospect of working with me

02:46.514 --> 02:50.518
again "a real life low."

02:50.561 --> 02:53.738
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
And that was after she called
him "a real lowlife."

02:53.782 --> 02:56.741
But money talks,
and the network met her price.

02:56.785 --> 02:58.700
So get ready to live on Mars.

03:09.754 --> 03:11.539
Uh, one more thing.

03:11.582 --> 03:12.757
Hmm.

03:12.801 --> 03:13.932
$7,500?

03:13.976 --> 03:15.934
Holy crap.

03:15.978 --> 03:19.242
I can... I can
actually pay my bills.

03:19.286 --> 03:21.766
And you'll get more
when you finish the script.

03:21.810 --> 03:23.725
Though, of course, you'll
have to split it with Dina.

03:23.768 --> 03:26.249
That's fine with me,
I'm just, uh...

03:26.293 --> 03:27.946
RAMOS:
So overwhelmed.

03:27.990 --> 03:30.079
You're right,
taking out the sweaters.

03:30.122 --> 03:32.342
See? I have no idea
what to pack.

03:32.386 --> 03:34.779
I mean, I've never
even been to Houston.

03:34.823 --> 03:37.217
What am I supposed to do there?

03:37.260 --> 03:40.263
Eat barbecue
and talk about the Astros?

03:40.307 --> 03:42.570
PETRA:
Always a good idea to talk
about football in Texas.

03:42.613 --> 03:46.487
The Astros are
baseball, not football.

03:46.530 --> 03:49.229
Same difference.

03:49.272 --> 03:52.841
You know, it's funny,
I never saw myself

03:52.884 --> 03:56.671
working for a non-profit,
or in public policy,

03:56.714 --> 03:59.282
but...

03:59.326 --> 04:04.244
I should at least
go check it out, right?

04:04.287 --> 04:05.767
Yes, absolutely.

04:05.810 --> 04:07.421
This is a really
good opportunity,

04:07.464 --> 04:10.424
and you shouldn't
second-guess it.

04:10.467 --> 04:13.253
What's taking you
so long in there?Here I come.

04:16.647 --> 04:19.998
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Oh, hey,
it's Houston Petra, y'all.

04:23.175 --> 04:25.221
Wow.I wanted to show you

04:25.265 --> 04:27.092
that when I come to Houston,
I can fit

04:27.136 --> 04:29.443
right in with all
your new friends.

04:29.486 --> 04:31.314
You're really sweet...

04:32.446 --> 04:34.056
...and so crazy.

04:34.099 --> 04:37.538
Look, if we have to do
long distance, we will.

04:37.581 --> 04:39.888
I'm sorry, Petra, that hair...

04:39.931 --> 04:42.325
Oh, I'm not Petra.

04:42.369 --> 04:44.458
No, I'm Patti, tonight.

04:44.501 --> 04:47.417
Well, come here, Patti.

04:47.461 --> 04:49.419
MARLENE:
I'm so into this.

04:49.463 --> 04:51.726
The writing is great,
the story moves,

04:51.769 --> 04:53.249
this first chapter just works.

04:53.293 --> 04:54.772
Who is your mentor?

04:54.816 --> 04:57.427
Oh, right, me.

04:57.471 --> 05:00.604
Marlene, what has gotten
into you? You're so happy.

05:00.648 --> 05:02.693
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Yeah, I don't think
I've ever seen

05:02.737 --> 05:05.000
Marlene's teeth before.
They are white.

05:05.043 --> 05:07.437
Because the writing is so great.

05:08.612 --> 05:12.007
Okay, and I also
have a new lover!

05:12.050 --> 05:14.705
But really, I would
have been this happy anyway,

05:14.749 --> 05:16.359
because of your writing.

05:16.403 --> 05:18.492
Okay, a click less happy
but still very happy.

05:18.535 --> 05:20.189
You're doing
great, Jane.

05:20.232 --> 05:21.277
Keep it up.

05:21.321 --> 05:23.497
Thank you. I-I plan to.

05:23.540 --> 05:25.499
Although,
now I have to divide my time

05:25.542 --> 05:28.589
between my novel
and my dad's telenovela.

05:28.632 --> 05:30.373
Oh, well, don't lose focus
on your novel.

05:30.417 --> 05:32.680
Because I would love to show it
to a friend in the industry.

05:32.723 --> 05:34.595
Really? That would be...Okay, okay.

05:34.638 --> 05:36.858
The friend is actually my lover.

05:36.901 --> 05:39.687
She's in publishing,
and she's a genius.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.732
That's amazing.She's amazing.

05:41.776 --> 05:44.909
You're amazing.
Write that novel, you have to.

05:44.953 --> 05:47.564
I will. I will work on it
in the mornings,

05:47.608 --> 05:49.392
and the telenovela
in the afternoons.

05:49.436 --> 05:51.394
I will have new material
for you to show your lover

05:51.438 --> 05:53.048
in a couple weeks.

05:53.091 --> 05:55.224
Great. We'll probably
be married by then.

05:55.267 --> 05:56.747
Oh!
I'm kidding.

05:56.791 --> 05:58.401
Oh, maybe I'm not. Ah!

05:58.445 --> 05:59.881
Okay, I got to go.

05:59.924 --> 06:01.317
I have a meeting
with Mateo's teacher.

06:01.361 --> 06:03.972
He's having trouble
learning to read.

06:04.015 --> 06:05.190
Oh, that's funny,

06:05.234 --> 06:07.236
because you're a writer.

06:07.279 --> 06:09.064
Yeah, funny.

06:09.107 --> 06:10.935
Hadn't thought of that.

06:13.329 --> 06:15.505
You seem a little
wired this morning.

06:15.549 --> 06:17.812
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR :
Maybehe has a new lover.

06:17.855 --> 06:20.423
I am just excited.

06:20.467 --> 06:23.339
I am close to selling
my first million dollar house,

06:23.383 --> 06:24.688
and there is a couple coming

06:24.732 --> 06:27.299
for their second appointment
this week.

06:27.343 --> 06:29.476
Ms. Everette, hi.Thanks for coming in.

06:29.519 --> 06:30.781
Thank you.
Of course.So I just thought

06:30.825 --> 06:32.261
we should discuss
Mateo's progress.

06:32.304 --> 06:34.959
Great. We wanted to
check in, too. At home,

06:35.003 --> 06:37.614
his rhyming is improving, but
he'd still rather build castles

06:37.658 --> 06:39.790
with his flashcards
than do his work.

06:39.834 --> 06:41.575
Yeah, but who wouldn't?I wouldn't.

06:41.618 --> 06:43.533
Besides you.Well, one
of the reasons

06:43.577 --> 06:46.841
I called you in is because I'm
wondering whether there might be

06:46.884 --> 06:49.539
something else
going on with Mateo.

06:49.583 --> 06:50.975
There's no cause
for alarm,

06:51.019 --> 06:52.890
but sometimes
when kids are struggling

06:52.934 --> 06:54.718
more than they should,
just, you know,

06:54.762 --> 06:56.241
makes sense to have them tested.

06:57.286 --> 07:00.463
Uh, tested for what, exactly?

07:00.507 --> 07:03.597
Could be any number of things.
Could be a learning disability,

07:03.640 --> 07:05.555
it could be a sensory
processing disorder,

07:05.599 --> 07:07.775
ADHD, dyslexia,

07:07.818 --> 07:09.298
or it could be nothing at all.

07:09.341 --> 07:11.169
This just could be who Mateo is.

07:11.213 --> 07:12.780
But there's
enough red flags

07:12.823 --> 07:14.259
that I do think it's worthwhile,

07:14.303 --> 07:16.479
having him evaluated
by a professional.

07:20.309 --> 07:23.486
So, uh, I'll call the doctor
and make an appointment today.

07:23.530 --> 07:25.575
You really think
that's necessary?

07:25.619 --> 07:26.750
He's only six.

07:26.794 --> 07:28.143
And the teacher
said it herself,

07:28.186 --> 07:30.145
it all might just be
his personality.

07:30.188 --> 07:32.930
But she also said she thought
Mateo should get tested.

07:32.974 --> 07:35.629
Well, I don't want to. No.

07:35.672 --> 07:37.500
Wait, what do you mean, "No"?

07:37.544 --> 07:39.328
He's just a kid
with a lot of energy.

07:39.371 --> 07:41.025
I had a lot of energy
when I was a kid.

07:41.069 --> 07:43.767
Uh, boys in general
have a lot of energy.

07:43.811 --> 07:46.291
Great, so then what's the harm
of getting him tested?

07:46.335 --> 07:47.989
Because they'll find something,
even if there's nothing to find.

07:48.032 --> 07:50.121
People these days, they hand out
diagnoses like Halloween candy.

07:50.165 --> 07:53.168
I'm sorry,
but I am putting my foot down.

07:53.211 --> 07:55.475
You're putting your foot down?

07:55.518 --> 07:57.912
He is not getting tested,
end of story.

07:59.043 --> 08:02.307
Now I got to get back to work.

08:02.351 --> 08:03.700
"End of story."

08:03.744 --> 08:05.528
Well, you know what?

08:05.572 --> 08:09.184
I'm the writer,
I'll end the story.

08:09.227 --> 08:11.186
Hi, this is Jane Villanueva.
I'd like to make

08:11.229 --> 08:14.189
an urgent appointment for my son
as soon as possible.

08:14.232 --> 08:16.365
Yes, I'll hold.

08:21.022 --> 08:22.589
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Man, I can't believe Jane made

08:22.632 --> 08:25.417
that doctor's appointment
behind Rafael's back.

08:25.461 --> 08:26.723
Oops. Wrong appointment.

08:26.767 --> 08:27.942
Boy, I really got to focus.

08:27.985 --> 08:29.509
Hi, good to see you.

08:29.552 --> 08:31.293
Let's jump in. I have
a lot of notes, and we need

08:31.336 --> 08:34.557
to turn a finished script in
to the studio in two weeks.

08:34.601 --> 08:35.689
Wow, that fast, huh?

08:35.732 --> 08:37.473
Yeah. That's how it works in TV.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.780
Everybody's on deadline
all the time, and we need to do

08:39.823 --> 08:41.477
rounds and rounds
of rewrites for the studio

08:41.521 --> 08:42.870
and then again
for the network.

08:42.913 --> 08:44.088
The work never stops.

08:45.176 --> 08:46.264
Is that too much for you?

08:46.308 --> 08:47.744
Of course not.
Agreed.

08:47.788 --> 08:49.441
Of course not. I'm
excited to get started.

08:49.485 --> 08:51.008
ROGELIO: All right,
the dream team.

08:51.052 --> 08:54.795
With your talent and passion
combined with Dina's

08:54.838 --> 08:57.449
decades of experience...One more thing.

08:57.493 --> 08:59.843
I will only speak to you.

08:59.887 --> 09:02.150
Any thoughts
your dad may have

09:02.193 --> 09:05.240
must only be relayed
through you.

09:05.283 --> 09:06.110
What?

09:08.635 --> 09:11.420
Uh, ask her "What?"

09:11.463 --> 09:13.901
What?
No need for "what."
You got it.

09:13.944 --> 09:17.165
Now your father needs to leave
so I can give you my notes.

09:17.208 --> 09:20.690
Dina, I assure you,
I'll be nothing but...Jane?

09:20.734 --> 09:22.910
Is someone speaking?

09:22.953 --> 09:25.390
You know what, Dad? Maybe
it's best if you go.

09:25.434 --> 09:27.915
Dina and I can take
care of it from here.

09:27.958 --> 09:30.047
Uh...

09:30.091 --> 09:32.093
Of course.Okay.

09:40.318 --> 09:42.103
Dad...

09:43.234 --> 09:45.628
Okay. Let's get to work.

09:46.760 --> 09:48.370
It worked.

09:48.413 --> 09:50.198
Our scientists did it.

09:50.241 --> 09:53.636
They've made the air
sustainable for life,

09:53.680 --> 09:56.247
which resulted in this...

09:56.291 --> 09:57.640
Wow...

09:57.684 --> 10:00.600
...the first-ever
Martian flower.

10:00.643 --> 10:03.951
It is an amazing achievement
for our administration.

10:03.994 --> 10:06.431
Wow. This should be the symbol

10:06.475 --> 10:08.782
on the new
Martian-American flag.

10:08.825 --> 10:11.523
Crumple it.

10:12.612 --> 10:13.743
Crumple the flower.

10:13.787 --> 10:15.484
Don't listen to
that Earth child.

10:15.527 --> 10:17.660
You can't crumple the
first Martian flower.

10:17.704 --> 10:20.315
See?

10:20.358 --> 10:22.317
That's what happens
to your virginity.

10:22.360 --> 10:25.886
Once it's gone,
you can never, ever get it back.

10:25.929 --> 10:27.627
Please,
it's a little late for that.

10:27.670 --> 10:30.891
My flower's been crumpled
for 96 Martian years.

10:30.934 --> 10:34.459
What is she talking about?
What is this?

10:50.519 --> 10:52.086
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Good, Jane.

10:52.129 --> 10:54.349
Focus on the telenovela.

10:54.392 --> 10:56.656
RAFAEL:
Flowers are not gonna make
me forgive you, Luisa.

10:56.699 --> 11:00.703
Your signature was
all over Rose's bank accounts.

11:00.747 --> 11:04.576
The woman can forge faces, I'm
sure she can forge a signature.

11:04.620 --> 11:06.840
I promise,
I'm not part of...

11:06.883 --> 11:09.712
whatever criminal things
she's doing.And I don't believe you.

11:09.756 --> 11:11.758
You have lied
too many times before.

11:11.801 --> 11:13.368
But I'm not lying now.

11:13.411 --> 11:16.414
Come on, Rafael.
Think of how far we've come.

11:16.458 --> 11:19.243
I'm sorry. Rose is too
dangerous. I can't risk it.

11:22.769 --> 11:25.380
How did it go?
Did he believe you?

11:25.423 --> 11:26.860
No.

11:26.903 --> 11:29.253
Well, don't give up, girl.

11:29.297 --> 11:30.690
Get him some proof
that you're innocent.

11:31.778 --> 11:33.736
You're so sweet to care so much.

11:33.780 --> 11:36.217
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Yeah, sweet, or diabolical,

11:36.260 --> 11:39.046
conniving and working for
your psychopath ex-girlfriend.

11:39.089 --> 11:41.875
Oh, you know
who you have to go see?Who?

11:41.918 --> 11:43.877
Your psychopath ex-girlfriend.

11:43.920 --> 11:44.791
"Sociopath."

11:44.834 --> 11:46.227
Oh, my bad. Mine, too.

11:46.270 --> 11:47.619
Maybe she could
help with proof.

11:47.663 --> 11:49.578
No. It's too hard
for me to see her.

11:49.621 --> 11:51.275
That woman's all hair
and cheekbones.

11:51.319 --> 11:53.408
Luisa, you are stronger
than you know.

11:53.451 --> 11:55.584
And your brother's
worth it, right?

11:55.627 --> 11:57.804
Come on. You got this, girl.

11:57.847 --> 11:59.240
PETRA:
Girls, Mommy needs

11:59.283 --> 12:00.458
some privacy. Stay in your room

12:00.502 --> 12:03.984
and play with your toys.

12:04.027 --> 12:05.812
RAMOS :
You've reached Jane Ramos.

12:05.855 --> 12:07.988
Please leave a message.Hey, J.R.,

12:08.031 --> 12:09.946
it's me. I'm-I'm sorry
I keep missing you.

12:09.990 --> 12:11.774
Call me back when you can.

12:11.818 --> 12:12.949
Oh, it's, uh,

12:12.993 --> 12:14.864
it's Patti, by the way.

12:14.908 --> 12:17.214
Who's Patti?:
Don't you knock?

12:17.258 --> 12:20.000
I did.
I guess Patti didn't hear me.

12:20.043 --> 12:21.610
Okay, well...

12:21.653 --> 12:24.221
if you must know,
J.R. is in Houston right now,

12:24.265 --> 12:25.832
and we haven't spoken
since she left.

12:25.875 --> 12:27.790
We keep missing each other.I'm sorry.

12:27.834 --> 12:30.097
That sucks. And Patti?

12:30.140 --> 12:31.446
Never mind about Patti.
Look, the girls

12:31.489 --> 12:32.708
will be ready for you
in a second. Girls!

12:32.752 --> 12:34.797
Uh-- stop playing. Let's go!

12:34.841 --> 12:36.799
Oh, I should warn you,
they're obsessed

12:36.843 --> 12:38.453
with their new circuit builder.

12:38.496 --> 12:40.107
They can't focus
on anything else.

12:40.150 --> 12:42.500
Maybe we should
have them tested, too.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.765
Uh, Mateo's teacher suggested

12:45.808 --> 12:47.810
getting him tested
for a learning disability

12:47.854 --> 12:50.073
or an attention thing
and Jane's all for it.

12:50.117 --> 12:53.207
But it's ridiculous,
because there's nothing wrong.

12:53.250 --> 12:54.164
Really?

12:54.208 --> 12:56.210
He's six. He's rambunctious.

12:56.253 --> 12:57.820
Or there's a real problem

12:57.864 --> 12:59.953
that needs to be addressed.There isn't.

12:59.996 --> 13:02.346
Rafael, your daughters
are in therapy,

13:02.390 --> 13:03.826
you're on antidepressants.

